# riel-cursor-cli-fable-impl-workflow

Use this skill only when the user explicitly asks for a Claude Fable 5, Fable,
or `claude-fable` implementation workflow.

For ordinary implementation work, the default package skill remains
`riel-cursor-cli-impl-workflow`, which runs
`cursor-cli-design-and-implement-review-loop` with GPT-5.5 design/review and
Composer 2.5 implementation. Do not select this Fable workflow merely because
the work is difficult.

This file is packaged under `skills/cursor`, so project-scope package checkout
projects it to `.cursor/rules/riel-cursor-cli-fable-impl-workflow.mdc` for
Cursor and Cursor CLI runs from that project. Cursor rules are not projected for
user-scope installs.

## Workflow

Use the packaged workflow bundle:

- Workflow id: `cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop`
- Package id: `cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop`

Preferred entry point from the repository root:

```bash
bun run packages/rielflow/src/bin.ts workflow package checkout cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop
bun run packages/rielflow/src/bin.ts workflow run cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop --output json
```

Equivalent direct command:

```bash
rielflow workflow package checkout cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop
rielflow workflow run cursor-cli-fable-design-and-implement-review-loop --output json
```

## Model Routing

This workflow uses `cursor-cli-agent` throughout.

- Review agent steps: `claude-fable-5`
- Implementation step: `composer-2.5`
- Design and other agent steps: `claude-opus-4-8`

The implementation step includes its self-review prompt variant because that
variant belongs to the same workflow node.

## Runtime Inputs

Run the workflow in issue-resolution mode for normal implementation work.

Pass structured workflow input through `--variables` when the task needs
explicit issue/reference context. Typical fields:

- `workflowInput.issueUrl`
- `workflowInput.issueNumber`
- `workflowInput.issueRepository`
- `workflowInput.issueTitle`
- `workflowInput.issueBody`
- `workflowInput.targetFeatureArea`
- `workflowInput.requestedBehavior`
- `workflowInput.cursorCliAgentReferences`
- `workflowInput.referenceRepositoryRoot`
- `workflowInput.referenceRepositoryUrl`

Planning-only mode is available via:

- `workflowInput.executionMode: "design-plan-only"`

## Reporting

After the workflow finishes, report:

- workflow mode
- changed files
- verification commands
- commit message
- commit hash
- pushed remote and branch

If the workflow fails because `rielflow` appears incorrect, switch to the
current repository's fix workflow.
